    <body>

        <div xml:id="AN143.2-kilavi">
          <p type="edition">poruḷvayiṟ piriyakkarutiya talaimakaṉait tōḻi talaimakaḷa tāṟṟāmai kaṇṭu tōḻi celavaḻuṅkuvittatu.</p>
          <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">How the confidante, seeing HER lack of strength, prevented HIM from going, who contemplated separation for the sake of wealth.</p>
        </div>
        <div xml:id="AN143.2">
            <lg type="edition">
              <l>ceyviṉaip pirita leṇṇik kaimmikak</l>
              <l>kāṭukavi ṉaḻiyak kaṭuṅkatir teṟutali</l>
              <l>ṉīṭuciṉai vaṟiya vāka volleṉa</l>
              <l>vāṭupa lakalilai kōṭaik koyyun</l>
              <l>tēkkama laṭukkat tāṅkaṇ mēkkeḻupu</l>
              <l>muḷiyariṟ piṟanta vaḷivaḷar kūreri</l>
              <l>cuṭarnimir neṭuṅkoṭi viṭarmukai muḻaṅkum</l>
              <l>vemmuṉai yaruñcura nīnti yaiya</l>
              <l>cēṟu meṉṟa ciṟucoṟ kivaṭkē</l>
              <l>vacaiyil vempōr vāṉavaṉ maṟava</l>
              <l>ṉacaiyil vāḻnarkku naṉkalañ curakkum</l>
              <l>poyyā vāyvāṭ puṇkaḻaṟ piṭṭaṉ</l>
              <l>maitava ḻuyarcimaik kutiraik kavāa</l>
              <l>ṉakalaṟai neṭuñcuṉait tuvalaiyiṉ malarnta</l>
              <l>taṇkamaḻ nīlam pōlak</l>
              <l>kaṇpaṉi yuḻantaṉa nōkō yāṉē.</l>
            </lg>
            <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                <l>Thinking of parting for the work to be done, (1a-c)</l>
                <l>there on the mountain side dense with teak trees, (5a-c)</l>
                <l>where, because of the fierce [sun] rays’ excessive scorching, so that the wild forest’s beauty perishes, (1df.)</l> 
                <l>the many moving/fading wide leaves are carried to the Kōṭai hill, (4)</l>
                <l>noisily, so that  the long branches become poor, (3)</l>
                <l>crossing the difficult desert on the hot frontier, oh lord, (8)</l>
                <l>where, rising to the heights, the glowing outstretched long banners of sharp flames</l>
                <l>growing in the wind, which were born from the dry thicket, thunder in cleft caves, (5d-7)</l>
                <l>because of those little words, “we will go”, as for her, (9)</l>
                <l>[her] eyes, (16a)</l>
                <l rend="indent4">like cool fragrant blue lotuses (15)</l>
                <l rend="indent4">that bloomed in the droplets from the vast mountain pools in the wide rocks (14)</l>
                <l rend="indent4">of the Kutirai slope with cloud-covered high peaks (13)</l>
                <l rend="indent4">of Pittaṉ, with a sword [and] scarring anklets , [whose] mouth does not lie, (12)</l>
                <l rend="indent4">the bold man of the Cēra king of flawless hot battle,</l>
                <l rend="indent4">who out of love showers good ornaments on those who live, (10f.)</l>
                <l>have started to bear tears. Ah, I ache. (16)</l>
            </lg>
        </div>
